Based off of installer presented at:  http://www.linuxjournal.com/node/1005818

Requires the apt package manager (debian, ubuntu,...).

You may be prompt you for your password:

•	If virtualenv is not installed, then the installer installs virtualenv as sudo.
•	The installer tries to install a symbolic link into $HOME/bin.
    If you do not have $HOME/bin, then /usr/local/bin will be used, which requires sudo.

To install, simply run:  ./scientist-installer.sh

When installed, you should be able to run:  scientist

